[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/basic_notrump"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH has a maximum 17 point 1NT opener.

NORTH has 9 points: 
- if SOUTH has 15 the total is 24, not enough for game. 
- if SOUTH has 17 the total is 26, enough for game. 
Since NORTH doesn't know what to do he passes the buck back to SOUTH 
by bidding 2NT; this is an invitation for SOUTH to bid game.

SOUTH has a maximum 17 point hand so she accepts the invitation.}

